{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Grpbpr1mNwmA95UYjuaSdu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The oracle checks:\n1. The `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret contains BOTH `ops-user` AND `report-user` in `users` and `users_roles` \n2. `ops-user` can authenticate and the cluster is yellow/green\n3. `report-user` can read from the `app-data` index\n\nThe task is to:\n1. Merge `user-provided-file-realm` (report-user) into `es-file-realm-aggregate` (ops-user only)\n2. Mount `es-file-realm-aggregate` into the ES nodes so the file realm reads from it\n3. Configure `elasticsearch.yml` to use a file realm pointing to the mounted secret\n\nRight now both secrets exist separately and neither is mounted in the StatefulSet. I need to merge report-user into the aggregate secret, mount it in the pods, and ensure Elasticsearch is configured to read from that path. Let me check the StatefulSet to see how it's currently structured.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6659,"cache_read_input_tokens":36855,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6659},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b1d4aed-73e7-4df7-8b3f-9ec2d7b0e5c9","uuid":"5d47f514-5d2f-44f9-85c0-e39c9b88f023","request_id":"req_011CcQbqFXTuNxz34kzLcW92"}
