{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016BEbgR5EYoTLEJgTthVN8E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret only contained `ops-user`, and neither file-realm secret was mounted into the Elasticsearch pods. The `elasticsearch.yml` also lacked a file realm configuration.\n\n**Fix applied (3 steps):**\n\n1. **Merged the secrets** â€” appended `report-user`'s hashed credentials and `viewer:report-user` role mapping from `user-provided-file-realm` into `es-file-realm-aggregate`.\n\n2. **Patched the StatefulSet** â€” added a `file-realm` volume backed by `es-file-realm-aggregate` and three volumeMounts that place `users`, `users_roles`, and `roles.yml` into `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/` where ES reads the file realm.\n\n3. **Patched the ConfigMap** â€” added `xpack.security.authc.realms.file.file1.order: 0` and `native1.order: 1` so ES explicitly uses the file realm first during authentication.\n\nAfter the rolling restart completed, `ops-user` authenticates and has cluster health access, and `report-user` authenticates and can read the `app-data` index."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":854,"cache_read_input_tokens":52798,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":854},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b1d4aed-73e7-4df7-8b3f-9ec2d7b0e5c9","uuid":"b063de5c-ef91-4f4d-bb90-3b567de43aa9","request_id":"req_011CcQcJcGthThuRg8kqKGRy"}
